The paper discusses the design and performance of non-binary LDPC convolutional codes, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.CC). The paper also mentions simulation results, which suggests that the paper may fall under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI) or signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents a construction method for the codes, which could also place it under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
